#Kursi

A powerful **online currency exchange service** built with Node.js and Express.js.  
Easily convert between different currencies, get live exchange rates, and integrate it seamlessly into your online apps.

## 📄 Description

- [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [API Routes](#api-routes)
- [Environment Variables](#environment-variables)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [Folder Structure](#folder-structure)
- [Contributing](#contributing)

## 💻 Installation

````bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/online-currency-exchange.git
cd kursi
npm install

## Usage
npm run dev

## API Routes
GET /user/users
GET /user/:id
POST /auth/signup
POST /auth/login

## 🗝️ Environment Variables
Create a `.env` file in the root folder and add the following:

```env
PORT=3000
DATABASE_URL=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_super_secret_key

## ⚡ Technologies Used
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB + Mongoose
- bcryptjs (password hashing)
- JSON Web Token (JWT) for authentication
- dotenv (environment variable management)
- chalk (for colored terminal messages)

## 🗂️ Folder Structure
src/
│
├── config/
│ └── db.js # MongoDB connection setup
│
├── controllers/
│ └── auth/
│ └── user.controller.js # Handles user register/login logic
│ └── exchange.controller.js # Handles currency exchange logic
│
├── models/
│ └── user.model.js # User schema
│
├── routes/
│ ├── auth/
│ │ └── auth.routes.js # Auth routes (login/register)
│ └── user.routes.js # User routes (get user info)
│ └── exchange.routes.js # Currency exchange routes
│
├── utils/
│ └── user.utils.js # Helper functions for users
│ └── rate.utils.js # Helper functions for exchange rates
│
└── server.js # App entry point

## 🤝 Contributing
Contributions, issues, and feature requests are welcome!

If you'd like to contribute:

1. Fork the repository
2. Create a new branch (`git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name`)
3. Commit your changes (`git commit -m 'Add some feature'`)
4. Push to the branch (`git push origin feature/your-feature-name`)
5. Open a pull request

Please open an issue first to discuss major changes before submitting a pull request.
````
